btest(i, pos) is true if bit pos of integer i is 1.
Bit positions start at 0.

i = 0
  pos = 0  btest = F
  pos = 1  btest = F
  pos = 2  btest = F
  pos = 3  btest = F
  pos = 4  btest = F
  pos = 5  btest = F

i = 1
  pos = 0  btest = T
  pos = 1  btest = F
  pos = 2  btest = F
  pos = 3  btest = F
  pos = 4  btest = F
  pos = 5  btest = F

i = 2
  pos = 0  btest = F
  pos = 1  btest = T
  pos = 2  btest = F
  pos = 3  btest = F
  pos = 4  btest = F
  pos = 5  btest = F

i = 3
  pos = 0  btest = T
  pos = 1  btest = T
  pos = 2  btest = F
  pos = 3  btest = F
  pos = 4  btest = F
  pos = 5  btest = F

i = 10
  pos = 0  btest = F
  pos = 1  btest = T
  pos = 2  btest = F
  pos = 3  btest = T
  pos = 4  btest = F
  pos = 5  btest = F

some direct examples:
btest(10, 0) = F
btest(10, 1) = T
btest(10, 2) = F
btest(10, 3) = T
